  "question": "A new program had 60 downloads in the first month. The number of downloads in the second month was three times as many as the downloads in the first month, but then reduced by 30% in the third month. How many downloads did the program have total over the three months?",
  "prompt": "A new program had 60 downloads in the first month. The number of downloads in the second month was three times as many as the downloads in the first month, but then reduced by 30% in the third month. How many downloads did the program have total over the three months?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "366",
  "generated_text": "To find the total number of downloads over the three months, we need to calculate the downloads for each month and sum them up.\n\n**Step 1: Calculate the downloads in the second month.**\nThe problem states that the second month had three times as many downloads as the first month.\n$$ \\text{Downloads}_2 = 3 \\times \\text{Downloads}_1 $$\n$$ \\text{Downloads}_2 = 3 \\times 60 = 180 $$\n\n**Step 2: Calculate the downloads in the third month.**\nThe problem states that the third month had a reduction of 30% from the second month's count.\n$$ \\text{Reduction} = 30\\% \\text{ of } 180 = 0.30 \\times 180 = 54 $$\n$$ \\text{Downloads}_3 = \\text{Downloads}_2 - \\text{Reduction} $$\n$$ \\text{Downloads}_3 = 180 - 54 = 126 $$\nAlternatively, you can calculate it as $70\\%$ of 180:\n$$ 0.70 \\times 180 = 126 $$\n\n**Step 3: Calculate the total downloads over the three months.**\n$$ \\text{Total} = \\text{Downloads}_1 + \\text{Downloads}_2 + \\text{Downloads}_3 $$\n$$ \\text{Total} = 60 + 180 + 126 $$\n$$ \\text{Total} = 240 + 126 $$\n$$ \\text{Total} = 366 $$\n\nThe total number of downloads is 366.\n\n\\boxed{366}\n",
